&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dental Academic Recruitment 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part-funded NIHR Academic Clinical Fellowship in GDP/CDS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specialty/Function:&lt;/strong&gt;General Dental Practice/CDS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Indicative posts:&lt;/strong&gt;1&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duration:&lt;/strong&gt;3 years to commence September 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employer:&lt;/strong&gt;Lead Employer Trust hosted by Northumbria Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt;Newcastle University’s School of Dental Sciences&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&lt;/strong&gt;NHS Medical &amp; Dental&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type:&lt;/strong&gt;Fixed Term Temporary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours&lt;/strong&gt;: Full time Hours - applications for LTFT working are welcome&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Group:&lt;/strong&gt;Medical &amp; Dental&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Scheme:&lt;/strong&gt;Hospital Medical &amp; Dental Staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Allowances:&lt;/strong&gt;To be confirmed on appointment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applications Open: 27th October 2020 at 16:00pm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applications Close:&lt;/strong&gt; 10th November 2020 at 16:00pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date:&lt;/strong&gt;TBC - virtual&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited from General Dental Practitioners and Community Dental Services dentists for a NIHR Academic Clinical Fellowship in General Dental Practice/CDS within Health Education England working across the North East and North Cumbria, to start September 2021. The post holder will be based at Newcastle University School of Dental Sciences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part-funded Academic Clinical Fellowships (ACFs) are 3 year fixed-term national training posts. Trainees undertake 25% academic training over the term of the post. They will continue to spend the remaining 75% in their separate post working clinically in General Dental Practice/CDS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ACF trainees undertake a Research Training Programme provided by the University for which funding is provided by NIHR. They also are eligible for a £1,000 bursary per year to support research training activity (eg. to attend academic conferences).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ACF trainees would also normally complete and submit an external funding application for a research fellowship to enable them to complete a higher degree (PhD or research MD) following the completion of their ACF fixed-term post,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All Academic Clinical Fellowships are run-through posts. A trainee entering ACF would therefore be guaranteed continued training for 3 years, as long as they progress satisfactorily through their training via annual appraisal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No clinical benchmarking is required for this post.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications will be restricted to those candidates who meet the eligibility and entry criteria as outlined in the person specification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Health Education England working across the North East and North Cumbria operates a ‘lead employer’ arrangement and all of our Academic Clinical Fellows are employed by the ‘Lead Employer Trust’ hosted by Northumbria Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust for the duration of their training.&lt;/p&gt;
